.TH "of_dma_get_max_cpu_address" 9 "of_dma_get_max_cpu_address" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_dma_get_max_cpu_address \- Gets highest CPU address suitable for DMA
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "phys_addr_t" of_dma_get_max_cpu_address
.BI "(struct device_node *np "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "np" 12
The node to start searching from or NULL to start from the root
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Gets the highest CPU physical address that is addressable by all DMA masters
in the sub-tree pointed by np, or the whole tree if NULL is passed. If no
DMA constrained device is found, it returns PHYS_ADDR_MAX.
